cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CC, cs.IR 

This paper is focused on natural language processing (NLP) and specifically on the task of modeling verb argument expectations. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses structured and unstructured distributional models, which are common in machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.LG and cs.AI). Additionally, the paper evaluates the performance of different hypotheses, which could fall under the sub-categories of cs.CC (Computational Complexity) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
